                        </origin>
                        <provenance type="found">Discovered incorporated in the fabric of the N wall of Templenagriffin chapel at the probable early ecclesiastical site of <ref target="https://monasticon.celt.dias.ie/showrecord.php?id=226">Ard Ferta (Breanainn)</ref> (Moore, 2007, 37). Remains inside the walled burial ground include a cathedral building [St Brendan's], dated variously from the 11th to the 17th century, based on a study of its architecture. There are two other churches on the site, a late 12th-century church called 'Templenahoe' and a 15th-century chapel called 'Templenagriffin'. It is also the site of a round tower, which fell during a storm in 1771, and two ogham stones (Moore, 2007, 11, 37-8). Ardfert 1 (I-KER-001) is also from this location, though it was found in the middle of a nearby field. 
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">On site in the restored Templenagriffin chapel where it was examined and recorded for the Ogham in 3D project in 2014.
                        </provenance>
